      • add_impl

        private void add_impl(Command command)
        Adds a command immediately to the Scheduler. This should only be called in the run() loop. Any command with conflicting requirements will be removed, unless it is uninterruptable. Giving null does nothing.
        Parameters:
        command - the Command to add

      • run

        public void run()
        Runs a single iteration of the loop. This method should be called often in order to have a functioning Command system. The loop has five stages:
        1. Poll the Buttons
        2. Execute/Remove the Commands
        3. Send values to SmartDashboard
        4. Add Commands
        5. Add Defaults

      • registerSubsystem

        void registerSubsystem(Subsystem system)
        Registers a Subsystem to this Scheduler, so that the Scheduler might know if a default Command needs to be run. All Subsystems should call this.
        Parameters:
        system - the system
